content.description: Begin just right of an overhanging section, climbing up then traversing left past two bolts. Head straight up the thin seam, past a rusty piton to a ledge with some bushes on it. Pull the crux move over a roof flake, on another thin crack past another piton then reach the anchors.
content.protection: A few small cams and stoppers. 4 draws.
content.location: From the west end of the wall where the trail meets the crag, walk east until the trail starts to steepen again. The route is just right of a black and white overhang. Find the traversing bolts about 10' up.

content.description: A toprope route on the east side of the wall. Scramble up to a triangular overhanging section, climb through the steep and get situated on the face, which trends right directly above. An alternative is to head straight up through the thin crack.
content.protection: Top rope from bushes or boulders up top.
content.location: Right side of Aussie wall. Scramble up the right side to set an anchor.

content.description: A boulder move gains a ledge. Climb through a open book formation (crux). A few easier moves gets you to another ledge, and the anchors (shared with "put the wind up ya")
content.protection: Stoppers. Cams from Tips to 3" and a few draws.
content.location: The second route from the left. Look for the pile of large rocks at the base.
